    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the grill to high</p><p>Add your <strong>cherry tomatoes</strong> to a <strong>tin foil</strong>-lined baking tray with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/the-mother-of-all-savoury-french-toast-with-feta-avo-and-hot-honey/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Put the tray under the grill for 10-12 min or until the tomatoes are blistered and bursting</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/the-mother-of-all-savoury-french-toast-with-feta-avo-and-hot-honey/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Set aside 1<strong> egg[s]</strong> per person for later</p><p>Crack the <strong>remaining egg[s]</strong> into a large bowl with a splash of <strong>milk</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> and whisk until completely combined \u2013 this is your <strong>egg mix</strong></p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/the-mother-of-all-savoury-french-toast-with-feta-avo-and-hot-honey/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) over a medium-high heat with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong></p><p>Slice your <strong>brioche bun[s]</strong> in half (if required)</p><p>Dip the <strong>brioche halves</strong> into the<strong> egg mix </strong>until it's been absorbed by the bread</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/the-mother-of-all-savoury-french-toast-with-feta-avo-and-hot-honey/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Cook the <strong>soaked brioche</strong> for 3-4 min each side or until golden brown and crisp \u2013 this is your <strong>savoury French toast</strong></p><p>Tip: Cooking for 3 or more? Use 2 pans or cook in batches</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/the-mother-of-all-savoury-french-toast-with-feta-avo-and-hot-honey/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, heat a separate large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil </strong>over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, crack the <strong>remaining egg[s]</strong> into the pan and cook for 2-3 min or until done to your liking</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/the-mother-of-all-savoury-french-toast-with-feta-avo-and-hot-honey/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>When everything is nearly done, combine your <strong>honey</strong> and <strong>chilli flakes</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!) in a small bowl with 1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">1 1/2 tsp] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span> <strong>butter</strong></p><p>Put in the <strong>microwave</strong> for 30 secs or until warm and runny \u2013 this is your <strong>hot honey</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/the-mother-of-all-savoury-french-toast-with-feta-avo-and-hot-honey/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>savoury French toast</strong> topped with the <strong>smashed avocado</strong>, <strong>blistered tomatoes</strong> and a <strong>fried egg</strong></p><p>Crumble your <strong>feta </strong>over the top and drizzle with the <strong>hot honey</strong></p><p>Time to start your day!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
